item.title: CVE-2017-20065|2024-08-05T21:45:25.250Z -- supsystic -- popup%20plugin
item.description: A vulnerability was found in Supsystic Popup Plugin 1.7.6 and classified as problematic. This issue affects some unknown processing. The manipulation leads to cross-site request forgery. The attack may be initiated remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.
